      "retweeted_tweet_id": null,
      "text": "Henry Roldan Perez-Roblero, 21, of Guatemala, faces a felony charge in Florida for allegedly sexually assaulting a child under 12 — a capital felony punishable in the state by death.\n\nICE issued a detainer with law enforcement in Martin County, Florida, and will take custody of him in the event he is ever released. \n\n👉Unlike sanctuary jurisdiction officials, Florida officials honor our detainers.\n\nPerez-Roblero illegally entered the United States in Arizona in January 2021 and was released into the country. An immigration judge ordered him removed January 22, 2025.",
      "text_resolved": "Henry Roldan Perez-Roblero, 21, of Guatemala, faces a felony charge in Florida for allegedly sexually assaulting a child under 12 — a capital felony punishable in the state by death.\n\nICE issued a detainer with law enforcement in Martin County, Florida, and will take custody of him in the event he is ever released. \n\n👉Unlike sanctuary jurisdiction officials, Florida officials honor our detainers.\n\nPerez-Roblero illegally entered the United States in Arizona in January 2021 and was released into the country. An immigration judge ordered him removed January 22, 2025.",
